The evidence with the title 'Great Recession in the United States - Wikipedia ' says The Great Recession in the United States was a severe financial crisis combined with a deep recession . While the recession officially lasted from december 2007 to june 2009 , it took several years for the economy to recover to pre-crisis levels of employment and output .  ... According to the Department Of Labor , roughly 8.7 million jobs ( about 7%)  ... 
